---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import profile from "../assets/profile.jpg";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Adi"
  description="Who Adi is, what he believes about building secure systems, and why this blog exists."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Hi, I’m Adi.</h1>
    <p>
      I work in cybersecurity, and I’m most interested in the part most people
      skip: the trade-offs.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-main">
      <p>
        To me, security is rarely about finding the technically perfect
        solution. Every real decision means balancing security, engineering
        effort, operational complexity, cost, compliance, and business goals.
        That tension, choosing what is right for a system that has to ship,
        scale, and keep running, is what I find most interesting.
      </p>
      <p>
        I’m based in Singapore. Here I share what I learn from working with
        production systems, exploring new technologies, and trying to better
        understand the decisions behind them. I write about cybersecurity,
        cloud, DevOps, software engineering, and the broader engineering
        challenges that come with building and operating modern systems.
      </p>
      <p>This website is where I think in public.</p>
      <p>
        Some articles are technical deep dives. Others are troubleshooting
        guides, architectural discussions, or reflections on decisions that
        don’t always have a single right answer. Whenever I can, I try to
        explain not only how something works, but why a particular approach
        makes sense.
      </p>
      <p>
        Writing forces me to organize my thoughts, challenge my own
        assumptions, and explain complex ideas clearly. As I continue studying,
        this website will grow alongside me, capturing new ideas, projects,
        experiences, and the lessons that come from them.
      </p>
      <p>
        If something here helps you solve a problem, challenges your thinking,
        or gives you a different perspective, then it’s done its job.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-card" aria-label="Profile links">
      <Image
        class="about-photo"
        src={profile}
        alt="Adi"
        widths={[280, 560]}
        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 280px"
      />
      <h2>Profile</h2>
      <p>Adi</p>
      <dl>
        <div>
          <dt>Location</dt>
          <dd>Singapore</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Focus</dt>
          <dd>Cybersecurity, cloud security, DevSecOps</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/adiparamkusam/">LinkedIn</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/adi-param">GitHub</a>
    </aside>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
